Investor Martin Sosnoff said in astatement that he was disappointed in Caesars World Inc'sresponse to his 28 dlrs a share offer to buy the company.    The company had said the offer was inadequate and that itwas exploring restructuring or sale of the company to anotherparty.    Sosnoff said he believes the offer is fair to allshareholders. "My primary desire is still to sit down withmanagement to negotiate a friendly acquisition," he said. Reuter&#3;